{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":69523,"duration_api_ms":69381,"num_turns":9,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"6e7ee81b-ec44-450b-a3fb-b352a2eb40bc","total_cost_usd":0.3568425,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":28001,"cache_read_input_tokens":179207,"output_tokens":2055,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":28001,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":7,"outputTokens":2055,"cacheReadInputTokens":179207,"cacheCreationInputTokens":28001,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.31601975,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":25,"outputTokens":1539,"cacheReadInputTokens":67865,"cacheCreationInputTokens":21053,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.040822750000000005,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"All four amendments identify real defects in plan_hash provenance handling across the lineage system. Three are clear bugs that should be fixed; one (fr-11-fb2ec5ae) is already documented as a known limitation with a self-documenting comment and represents a design trade-off rather than an overlooked bug.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-11-8183a7c6","decision":"accept","rationale":"Valid edge case. When an entry is created before any plan is persisted, both plan_hash and snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation are None. The legacy guard at line 2639 treats this identically to genuinely legacy entries where provenance is unknown, but the semantics differ: a 'no plan yet' entry has a known empty provenance that can safely be upgraded. The proposed fix — allowing backfill when both fields are None AND the entry is still Running — is sound because no prior plan version could conflict. This is a real gap in the acceptance criterion coverage."},{"amendment_id":"fr-11-fb2ec5ae","decision":"reject","rationale":"The code at lines 3051-3063 already contains an explicit comment (lines 3054-3059) documenting this exact race as a 'Known limitation' and stating the long-term fix is for callers to supply plan_hash explicitly. This is a conscious design trade-off, not an overlooked bug. The race window (between dispatch and record_task_run_start) is narrow and the comment acknowledges the imprecision. Threading dispatch-time plan hash through every call path is a significant architectural change that goes beyond a targeted amendment — it's a tracked design debt item. Rejecting as a final-review amendment does not mean it shouldn't be done, but it's not a missed defect."},{"amendment_id":"fr-11-4bfe4027","decision":"accept","rationale":"Real bug in the duplicate-row repair path. Lines 3009-3010 find the first raw entry matching same_attempt, but in duplicate-row states this can be the stale copy with plan_hash=None while the canonical view (which merges duplicates) already has the populated metadata. The code then calls backfill_running_entry and safe_plan_hash_backfill on the stale row, which may not change it, and returns without repair. The fix should either use the canonical merged entry's metadata to inform the repair, or select the most complete raw duplicate as the repair target."},{"amendment_id":"fr-11-60e3c49b","decision":"accept","rationale":"Confirmed defect. merge_attempt_entries at lines 320-337 merges run_id, plan_hash, outcome_detail, started_at, and finished_at — but omits snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation entirely. Both collapse_task_run_group (line 641) and duplicate cleanup (lines 3310-3314) use merge_attempt_entries. If the primary row is the stale one (snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation=None) and the secondary has the provenance, the merge drops it permanently. After that, safe_plan_hash_backfill at line 2639 will see None and refuse to backfill, breaking the repair chain. Adding `if merged.snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation.is_none() { merged.snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation = secondary.snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation.clone(); }` to merge_attempt_entries is the straightforward fix."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"30b3da83-4081-47bc-9171-a9e03c51e8bc"}
